The paper deals with secure computation of a function using public communication, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves computation and communication complexity, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the capacity of a secrecy generation model, which could be related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
